20Southeast%20Asian%20nation.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20344px)%2085vw%2C%20344px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F29115330%2F71q7bLpIgkS._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22344%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F29115330%2F71q7bLpIgkS._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg%20656w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F29115330%2F71q7bLpIgkS._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-197x300.jpg%20197w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-694779%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22525%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EJessica%20Muddit%2C%3Cbr%3EOur%20Home%20in%20Myanmar%3Cbr%3ESelf%20published%20(2021)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMuddit%E2%80%99s%20book%20transcends%20this%20superficiality.%20Drawing%20upon%20her%20meticulous%20academic%20training%20and%20seasoned%20journalistic%20instincts%2C%20she%20offers%20a%20nuanced%20portrait%20of%20Myanmar%20during%20its%20tumultuous%20years%20from%202012%20to%202016.%20This%20period%20witnessed%20a%20brief%20flicker%20of%20democracy%20under%20Aung%20San%20Suu%20Kyi%2C%20before%20the%20military%20reasserted%20its%20grip.%20Muddit%E2%80%99s%20vivid%20chronicle%20provides%20not%20just%20a%20captivating%20read%20but%20also%20a%20treasure%20trove%20of%20insights%20for%20researchers%20across%20diverse%20disciplines.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20me%2C%20a%20personal%20revelation%20emerged%20from%20these%20pages%3A%20the%20vibrant%20state%20of%20freelance%20journalism%20in%20Myanmar.%20I%20was%20very%20surprised%20to%20learn%20that%20it%E2%80%99s%20actually%20possible%20to%20thrive%20as%20an%20independent%20journalist%2C%20selling%20stories%20to%20the%20local%20media%20%E2%80%93%20a%20stark%20contrast%20to%20the%20harsh%20realities%20of%20freelance%20journalism%20in%20my%20own%20country%2C%20Bangladesh.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EDecent%20living%20through%20freelance%20works%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%202012%2C%20Muddit%20moved%20to%20Myanmar%2C%20after%20her%20year-long%20stint%20in%20some%20Bangladeshi%20newspapers%2C%20to%20have%20a%20fresh%20start%20along%20with%20her%20Bangladeshi%20partner.%20There%2C%20her%20initial%20stint%20at%20%3Cem%3Ethe%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0Myanmar%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20ended%20abruptly%2C%20but%20instead%20of%20seeking%20another%20full-time%20position%2C%20she%20took%20a%20leap%20into%20freelance%20reporting.%20What%20she%20found%20surprised%20her%3A%20thriving%20local%20media%20outlets%20paying%20handsomely%20for%20quality%20content.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWith%20each%20piece%20fetching%20at%20least%20%24100%20and%20landing%2010-15%20commissions%20monthly%2C%20Muddit%20earned%20%241200-%241500%20which%20was%20enough%20for%20a%20comfortable%20upper-middle-class%20life%20in%20Yangon.%20This%2C%20in%20a%20country%20with%20an%20eighth%20the%20GDP%20and%20half%20the%20per%20capita%20income%20of%20Bangladesh!%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20the%20outset%2C%20it%20might%20seem%20baffling%20as%20Myanmar%2C%20riddled%20with%20decades%20of%20military%20rule%2C%20ethnic%20conflicts%2C%20and%20protectionist%20policies%2C%20ranks%20lower%20than%20Bangladesh%20in%20press%20freedom%20(173rd%20vs%20163rd).%20However%2C%20if%20someone%20delves%20deeper%20into%20the%20journalism%20practiced%20in%20the%20country%2C%20they%20would%20be%20surprised%20to%20find%20out%20that%20amidst%20this%20seemingly%20dystopian%20landscape%2C%20a%20few%20brave%20and%20truly%20independent%20publications%20like%20%3Cem%3EFrontier%20Myanmar%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20the%20%3Cem%3EIrrawaddy%3C%2Fem%3E%20are%20not%20only%20producing%20critical%20journalism%20under%20pressure%20but%20also%20thriving.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThese%20publications%20understand%20the%20value%20of%20their%20reporters%E2%80%99%20contributions%20and%20compensate%20them%20well%2C%20recognising%20that%20quality%20journalism%20demands%20fair%20pay%20and%20ensures%20the%20public%E2%80%99s%20right%20to%20know.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20is%20not%20unique%20to%20Myanmar.%20Even%20Nepal%20%E2%80%93%20way%20poorer%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20size%20and%20prospect%20of%20the%20economy%20%E2%80%93%20than%20Bangladesh%2C%20had%20the%20presence%20of%20strong%20independent%20media%20houses%20like%20%3Cem%3EHimal%20Southasian%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20the%20%3Cem%3ERecord%20Nepal%3C%2Fem%3E.%20The%20latter%20has%20seized%20their%20operations%20now%20because%20of%20financial%20constraints%20but%20they%20used%20to%20pay%20freelance%20reporters%20more%20than%20%24100-a-piece.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EWhy%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20the%20market%20thrived%20here%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20contrast%2C%20freelance%20reporters%20in%20Bangladesh%20rarely%20find%20opportunities%20beyond%20soft-feature%20pieces%20written%20from%20their%20desks.%20In-depth%20articles%20requiring%20fieldwork%20or%20research%20are%20practically%20nonexistent%20here.%20To%20add%20to%20that%2C%20payments%20are%20abysmal%20and%20usually%20hover%20around%20%2410-%2430%20per%20piece%2C%20making%20sustainable%20monthly%20wages%20nearly%20impossible.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fmaking-prothom-alo-the-enemy-in-bangladesh%5C%22%3EMaking%20Prothom%20Alo%20%E2%80%98the%20Enemy%E2%80%99%20in%20Bangladesh%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBesides%2C%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20shift%20towards%20authoritarianism%20has%20fostered%20a%20culture%20of%20%E2%80%98thank%20you%20journalism%E2%80%99%20where%20media%20outlets%20primarily%20parrot%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20narrative.%20This%20stifles%20critical%20reporting%2C%20a%20cornerstone%20of%20freelance%20journalism.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFreelance%20reporters%20often%20contribute%20to%20various%20publications%20to%20build%20their%20brand%20and%20credibility%2C%20aiming%20for%20opportunities%20with%20international%20outlets%20offering%20better%20pay.%20However%2C%20journalism%20aimed%20at%20only%20flattering%20the%20government%20could%20jeopardise%20these%20aspirations%2C%20as%20many%20international%20outlets%20frown%20upon%20such%20practices.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBangladesh%20mirrors%20the%20global%20trend%20of%20digital%20growth%20but%20this%20crucial%20element%20%E2%80%93%20a%20robust%20freelancing%20market%20%E2%80%93%20is%20completely%20absent%20here.%20That%E2%80%99s%20why%20newsrooms%20here%20fail%20to%20produce%20in-depth%20features%20or%20long-form%20articles%2C%20which%20most%20of%20the%20media%20houses%20in%20the%20West%20as%20well%20as%20in%20neighbouring%20India%20have%20started%20to%20outsource%20from%20a%20battery%20of%20freelancers%20%E2%80%93%20both%20for%20reduced%20cost%20and%20enhanced%20quality.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20lack%20of%20a%20freelance%20market%20not%20only%20puts%20immense%20pressure%20on%20existing%20journalists%2C%20juggling%20tighter%20deadlines%20and%20increased%20workloads%2C%20but%20also%20puts%20pressure%20on%20the%20media%20houses%20which%2C%20without%20quality%20content%2C%20cannot%20remain%20relevant%20to%20their%20readers.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EFaisal%20Mahmud%20is%20a%20journalist%20based%20in%20Dhaka.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706511604000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F29121654%2FUntitled-design-5-2.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fwhat-does-the-absence-of-freelance-journalism-in-bangladesh-tell-us%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20lack%20of%20a%20freelance%20market%20not%20only%20puts%20immense%20pressure%20on%20existing%20journalists%2C%20juggling