opposition%20leaders%2C%20as%20part%20of%20the%20Bharat%20Jodo%20Nyay%20Yatra%2C%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20spoke%20in%20favour%20of%20a%20collective%20fight%20to%20restore%20peace%20in%20Manipur.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20argument%20that%20the%20Bharat%20Jodo%20Yatra%20is%20aimed%20at%20getting%20electoral%20mileage%20for%20the%20Congress%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20stand%20here%20as%20the%20assembly%20elections%20in%20Manipur%20were%20held%20in%202022%2C%20with%20the%20Congress%20suffering%20its%20worst%20defeat%20in%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20elections%20in%20Manipur%20a%20good%20three%20years%20away%2C%20the%20Bharat%20Jodo%20Nyay%20Yatra%20instead%20chose%20to%20acknowledge%20the%20losses%20that%20the%20public%20of%20the%20state%20has%20suffered%20in%20the%20past%20year%2C%20a%20gesture%20that%20does%20amount%20to%20applying%20balm%20on%20scars%20that%20are%20not%20healing%C2%A0any%20time%20soon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELest%20we%20forget%2C%20Mahatma%20Gandhi%20gave%20us%20the%20talisman%20that%20whenever%20we%20are%20in%20doubt%2C%20we%20need%20to%20ask%20whether%20the%20step%20we%20take%20will%20lead%20to%20%3Cem%3Eswaraj%3C%2Fem%3E%20for%20the%20hungry%20and%20spiritually%20starving%20millions.%20The%20Bharat%20Jodo%20Yatra%20aims%20to%20build%20the%20Bharat%20of%20Mahatma%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20dreams.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fakhil-chaudhary%5C%22%3EAkhil%20Chaudhary%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20human%20rights%20lawyer%20based%20in%20Rajasthan.%20He%20posts%20on%20X%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fakhilchaudhary%5C%22%3E%40akhilchaudhary%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706443238000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F16091824%2FRG-in-Manipur-photo-by-congress-day-2-BJNY.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fwhy-theres-more-to-the-bharat-jodo-nyay-yatra-than-just-winning-elections%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20look%20at%20the%20states%20through%20which%20the%20Bharat%20Jodo%20Nyay%20Yatra%20is%20passing%20through%20reveals%20that%20there%E2%80%99s%20much%20more%20to%20the%20initiative%20than%20just%20winning%20elections.%20One%20example%20is%20Manipur%2C%20where%20assembly%20elections%20are%20three%20years%20away.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A30%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fwhy-theres-more-to-the-bharat-jodo-nyay-yatra-than-just-winning-elections%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Nitish's%20INDIA%20Exit%3A%20Why%20the%20Blame%20Rests%20on%20Mamata%20Banerjee%20and%20Arvind%20Kejriwal%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F28163221%2F400924413_926965212122173_7713585483950685171_n.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20After%20days%20of%20speculation%2C%20Bihar%20chief%20minister%20Nitish%20Kumar%20resigned%20from%20his%20position%20Sunday%20morning%2C%20after%20his%20party%20Janata%20Dal%20(United)%20decided%20to%20end%20its%20alliance%20with%20the%20Rashtriya%20Janata%20Dal.%20He%20then%20took%20oath%20as%20chief%20minister%20for%20the%20ninth%20time%20and%20formed%20a%20new%20government%20with%20the%20support%20of%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party.%20Over%20the%20last%20two%20months%2C%20rumours%20that%20Nitish%20may%20join%20the%20BJP-led%20National%20Democratic%20Alliance%20again%20had%20been%20rife%20but%20the%20chief%20minister%E2%80%99s%20silence%20over%20the%20matter%2C%20even%20as%20he%20publicly%20expressed%20his%20anguish%20over%20lack%20of%20any%20progress%20in%20the%20INDIA%20bloc%20at%20least%20twice%2C%20left%20the%20political%20pot%20boiling.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20only%20after%20submitting%20his%20resignation%20to%20the%20governor%2C%20Rajendra%20Arlekar%2C%20on%20Sunday%20morning%20that%20Nitish%20confirmed%20all%20rumours%2C%20giving%20little%20chance%20to%20his%20former%20allies%20in%20INDIA%20to%20negotiate%2C%20cajole%20or%20convince%20him%20to%20stay%20in%20the%20opposition%20alliance.%20This%20lent%20further%20credence%20to%20the%20impression%20that%20Nitish%20had%20already%20decided%20to%20part%20ways%20with%20the%20opposition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20have%20resigned%20as%20CM%20today%20and%20have%20asked%20the%20Governor%20to%20put%20an%20end%20to%20this%20government.%20Party%20leaders%20were%20giving%20me%20advice.%20I%20heard%20what%20they%20said%20and%20have%20resigned.%20The%20situation%20was%20not%20good.%20So%2C%20we%20have%20broken%20ties%2C%E2%80%9D%20Nitish%20said%20in%20his%20usual%20taciturn%20style%20while%20announcing%20his%20decision%2C%20but%20more%20importantly%20added%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20were%20working%20on%20an%20alliance%20(INDIA)%20for%20the%20last%201.5%20years%20but%20things%20were%20not%20working%20out.%20Now%2C%20we%20will%20form%20a%20new%20alliance.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELike%20in%20the%20past%2C%20when%20he%20similarly%20switched%20camps%2C%20he%20evaded%20appearing%20in%20the%20public%20to%20clarify%20doubts%2C%20remained%20unreachable%20to%20his%20allies%20who%20attempted%20to%20contact%20him%20multiple%20times%2C%20and%20focused%20solely%20on%20mapping%20out%20the%20contours%20of%20the%20deal%20with%20the%20saffron%20party%20ahead%20of%20the%202024%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EChasing%20Nitish%E2%80%99s%20political%20ambitions%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEver%20since%20Nitish%20secured%20his%20first%20full-term%20tenure%20as%20the%20chief%20minister%20in%202005%2C%20he%20has%20barely%20been%20in%20an%20oppositional%20space.%20Barring%20a%20few%20months%20here%20and%20there%2C%20every%20decision%20that%20the%20septuagenarian%20leader%20took%20reasserted%20his%20own%20indispensability%20in%20Bihar%2C%20even%20when%20making%20new%20alliances.%20He%20has%20survived%2C%20and%20survived%20beyond%20anyone%E2%80%99s%20imagination%2C%20while%20remaining%20in%20power%20or%20pulling%20the%20strings%20of%20power%20ceaselessly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20little%20doubt%20that%20Nitish%20had%20his%20own%20political%20ambitions%20in%20mind%20every%20time%20he%20switched%20camps.%20He%20remained%20with%20the%20BJP%20to%20compete%20with%20the%20primary%20rival%20RJD%20in%20Bihar%20for%20years%2C%20but%20ended%20this%20alliance%20as%20he%20could%20foresee%20the%20fate%20of%20allies%20with%20the%20seemingly%20totalitarian%20Narendra%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20ascent%20at%20the%20Centre.%20Nitish%20recharged%20his%20own%20position%20by%20quitting%20the%20NDA%20and%20beating%20the%20BJP%20with%20the%20help%20of%20its%20arch%20rival%20RJD%20in%20the%202015%20state%20assembly%20polls.%20Having%20delivered%20a%20striking%20message%20to%20Modi%20about%20his%20political%20significance%2C%20he%20went%20back%20to%20the%20NDA%20where%20he%20had%20been%20the%20most%20comfortable%20in%20his%20career.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20relationship%20with%20the%20BJP%2C%20however%2C%20took%20the%20biggest%20hit%20when%20the%20Modi-Shah%20duo%20allegedly%20engineered%20substantial%20losses%20for%20the%20Janata%20Dal%20(United)%20with%20the%20help%20of%20Lok%20Janshakti%20Party%E2%80%99s%20Chirag%20Paswan%20in%20the%202020%20assembly%20polls.%20BJP%2C%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20state%E2%80%99s%20history%2C%20ended%20up%20with%20its%20best%20tally%20(74)%2C%20while%20Janata%20Dal%20finished%20with%20one%20of%20its%20worst%20performances%20as%20a%20NDA%20constituent%20with%20merely%2043%20seats.%20Things%20took%20a%20final%20hit%20when%20he%20lost%20his%20closest%20aide%20R.C.P.%20Singh%20to%20the%20BJP.%20Singh%20was%20swiftly%20made%20a%20Union%20minister%2C%20even%20as%20the%20BJP%20attempted%20to%20poach%20JD(U)%E2%80%99s%20legislators.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENitish%20was%20at%20the%20time%20the%20only%20prominent%20BJP%20ally%20in%20India%20as%20others%20like%20Shiv%20Sena%2C%20Shiromani%20Akali%20Dal%20(Badal)%20or%20Telugu%20Desam%20Party%20had%20already%20left%20the%20NDA%20because%20of%20the%20Modi-Shah%20duo%E2%80%99s%20alleged%20disregard%20for%20alliance%20politics.%20Yet%2C%20Nitish%20survived%20by%20quickly%20joining%20ranks%20with%20the%20RJD%2C%20this%20time%20with%20a%20national%20goal%20to%20help%20create%20a%20larger%20opposition%20front%20against%20the%20Modi-led%20BJP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENitish%20is%20now%20back%20in%20the%20NDA%2C%20masterfully%20securing%20his%20position%20as%20the%20most%20valuable%20ally%20of%20the%20BJP%20in%20Bihar%20yet%20again.%20The%20saffron%20party%20hadn%E2%80%99t%20missed%20a%20window%20to%20clamp%20down%20on%20Nitish%20in%20the%20last%20two%20years.%20Its%20senior%20leaders%20hit%20out%20at%20Nitish%20on%20almost%20a%20daily%20basis%2C%20with%20even%20the%20prime%20minister%20lashing%20out%20at%20him%20quite%20a%20few%20times%20in%20his%20speeches.%20Nitish%E2%80%99s%20rule%20was%20compared%20by%20the%20BJP%20to%20a%20%3Cem%3Ejungle%20raaj%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20as%20BJP%20leaders%20built%20a%20campaign%20around%20alleged%20corruption%2C%20misgovernance%2C%20and%20failing%20law%20and%20order%20in%20Bihar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHow%20Nitish%20operated%20through%20this%20mesh%20of%20political%20dynamics%20is%20known%2C%20but%20by%20accepting%20him%20again%2C%20the%20Modi-led%20BJP%20has%20shown%20that%20it%20prioritises%20its%20electoral%20ambitions%20much%20more%20than%20its%20rhetoric%20of%20good%20governance%20and%20political%20ethics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20big%20blow%20for%20INDIA%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Nitish%E2%80%99s%20exit%20will%20come%20as%20a%20cruel%20blow%20for%20the%20INDIA%20bloc.%20In%20more%20ways%20than%20one%2C%20Nitish%20was%20the%20chief%20architect%20of%20INDIA.%20Over%20the%20last%20two%20years%2C%20he%20had%20handed%20over%20Bihar%E2%80%99s%20reins%20to%20his%20deputy%20Tejashwi%20Yadav%2C%20while%20touring%20the%20country%20to%20bring%20together%20a%20range%20of%20regional%20and%20national%20parties%20under%20a%20common%20umbrella.%20Most%20of%20these%20parties%20have%20been%20historically%20inimical%20to%20the%20Congress.%20Bringing%20them%20all%20together%20to%20ally%20with%20the%20Congress%20required%20negotiations%20that%20only%20a%20senior%20leader%20with%20political%20acumen%20like%20Nitish%20could%20have%20done.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20he%20was%20instrumental%20in%20conducting%20a%20caste%20survey%20in%20Bihar%2C%20which%20gave%20a%20fillip%20to%20the%20opposition%20parties%2C%20including%20the%20Congress.%20The%20demand%20for%20a%20pan-India%20caste%20census%20re-energised%20Mandal%20politics%20and%20put%20the%20BJP%20on%20the%20backfoot%2C%20even%20if%20temporarily.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20the%20Nitish%20government%20foregrounded%20issues%20like%20employment%20and%20welfare%20in%20the%20last%20few%20months%20by%20appointing%20over%20three%20lakh%20youth%20in%20state%20government%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20initial%20success%20of%20INDIA%20as%20a%20front%2C%20that%20also%20fended%20off%20the%20possibility%20of%20a%20third%20front%20in%202024%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls%2C%20the%20Bihar%20chief%20minister%20displayed%20his%20frustration%20with%20its%20lack%20of%20progress.%20His%20first%20dissent%20came%20in%20November%202023%20when%20he%20showed%20his%20anguish%20over%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Ffor-india-to-work-the-congress-must-take-a-step-back%5C%22%3Elethargic%20approach%20towards%20the%20opposition%20front%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20a%20time%20when%20the%20grand-old%20party%E2%80%99s%20sole%20focus%20was%20on%20the%20assembly%20polls%20in%20five%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Congress%20lost%20all%20the%20three%20Hindi-heartland%20states%2C%20despite%20showing%20great%20confidence%20in%20the%20run-up%20to%20the%20polls.%20However%2C%20if%20someone%20needs%20to%20take%20the%20blame%20in%20triggering%20Nitish%E2%80%99s%20exit%2C%20they%20will%20have%20to%20be%20the%20chief%20ministers%20of%20West%20Bengal%20and%20Delhi%2C%20Mamata%20Banerjee%20and%20Arvind%20Kejriwal.%20The%20two%20leaders%20mooted%20the%20idea%20of%20making%20Congress%20president%20Mallikarjun%20Kharge%20INDIA%E2%80%99s%20prime%20ministerial%20candidate%20in%20the%20long-delayed%20INDIA%20meeting%20in%20New%20Delhi%20on%20December%2019%2C%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20meeting%20called%20by%20the%20Congress%20was%20supposed%20to%20happen%20on%20December%206%2C%202023%20but%20leaders%20like%20Banerjee%20and%20Kejriwal%20expressed%20their%20unavailability%2C%20indicating%20their%20discomfort%20with%20the%20alliance.%20Then%2C%20when%20the%20meeting%20happened%20eventually%2C%20the%20two%20leaders%20surprisingly%20floated%20the%20idea%20of%20Kharge%20as%20the%20prime%20ministerial%20candidate%20without%20discussing%20it%20with%20any%20of%20the%20other%20leaders.%20This%20was%20at%20a%20time%20when%20the%20Congress%20was%20recovering%20from%20its%20losses%20in%20assembly%20elections%20and%20had%20a%20lot%20of%20explaining%20to%20do%20in%20front%20of%20its%20partners.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20discussions%20on%20prime%20ministerial%20candidates%20appeared%20to%20be%20premature%2C%20when%20basics%20like%20seat-sharing%2C%20campaign%20strategy%20and%20joint%20action%20programmes%20had%20not%20been%20finalised.%20The%20fact%20that%20TMC%20spokespersons%20went%20on%20record%20after%20the%20fourth%20INDIA%20meeting%20on%20December%2019%20to%20suggest%20that%20INDIA%20will%20finalise%20seat-sharing%20by%20December%2031%20also%20looked%20improbable%2C%20forcing%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20general%20secretary%20(organisation)%20K.C.%20Venugopal%20and%20RJD%20chief%20Lalu%20Prasad%20to%20refute%20the%20TMC%20in%20their%20statements.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20may%20recall%20how%20Nitish%20had%20braved%20media%20questions%20on%20a%20probable%20prime%20ministerial%20candidate%20for%20the%20INDIA%20bloc%20when%20he%20was%20meeting%20leaders%20to%20formalise%20the%20alliance.%20Having%20known%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20preference%20to%20reduce%20the%202024%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls%20into%20a%20%E2%80%9CModi%20vs%20%E2%80%98who%E2%80%99%E2%80%9D%20presidential%20style%2C%20Nitish%20had%20floated%20the%20idea%20of%20a%20%E2%80%9Ccollective%20leadership%E2%80%9D%20in%20INDIA%20and%20persistently%20maintained%20that%20the%20alliance%20will%20fight%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls%20by%20highlighting%20the%20concerns%20of%20common%20people%20and%20canvassing%20against%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20alleged%20authoritarian%20and%20centralising%20impulses.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20mischievous%20moves%20by%20Banerjee%20and%20Kejriwal%2C%20who%20have%20now%20made%20their%20minds%20clear%20by%20announcing%20that%20there%20will%20be%20no%20alliance%20with%20the%20Congress%20in%20West%20Bengal%20and%20Punjab%2C%20undermined%20Nitish%20and%20other%20regional%20leaders%20of%20INDIA%2C%20and%20created%20a%20political%20narrative%20that%20was%20vastly%20different%20from%20what%20INDIA%20leaders%20had%20originally%20intended.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGiven%20how%20Nitish%20had%20already%20expressed%20his%20view%20about%20the%20supposed%20%E2%80%9Clack%20of%20seriousness%E2%80%9D%20in%20India%2C%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20hasty%20decision%20to%20train%20its%20energy%20on%20the%20second%20round%20of%20the%20Bharat%20Jodo%20Nyay%20Yatra%20in%20the%20run-up%20to%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls%2C%20even%20before%20the%20alliance%E2%80%99s%20campaign%20strategy%20was%20chalked%20out%2C%20may%20have%20come%20as%20a%20final%20nail%20in%20the%20coffin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENitish%20has%20not%20bothered%20with%20monikers%20like%20%E2%80%9Cchameleon%E2%80%9D%20or%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Ekursi%3C%2Fem%3E%20(chair)%20Kumar%E2%80%9D%20or%20even%20%E2%80%9Cpaltu%20ram%E2%80%9D%20thrown%20at%20him%20ever%20in%20his%20political%20career.%20He%20has%20never%20owned%20ideological%20ethics.%20He%20has%20rather%20taken%20pride%20in%20his%20pragmatism%20and%20effectiveness.%20With%20Nitish%E2%80%99s%20exit%2C%20the%20formidable%20opposition%20alliance%20in%20Bihar%20and%20its%2040%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats%20has%20broken.%20The%20INDIA%20bloc%2C%20too%2C%20will%20sorely%20miss%20his%20strategic%20thinking%20and%20political%20acumen%20in%20taking%20on%20the%20dominant%20BJP.%20Nitish%20could%20have%20been%20an%20asset%20for%20the%20alliance%2C%20given%20his%20deep%20political%20experience%20in%20the%20Hindi%20heartland.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706439998000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F28163221%2F400924413_926965212122173_7713585483950685171_n.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fnitish-kumar-india-alliance-exit%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Nitish%E2%80%99s%20exit%20will%20come%20as%20a%20cruel%20blow%20for%20the%20INDIA%20bloc.%20In%20more%20ways%20than%20one%2C%20Nitish%20was%20the%20chief%20architect%20of%20INDIA.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fnitish-kumar-india-alliance-exit%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22For%20the%20ICJ%20to%20Say%20It%20Is%20'Plausible'%20That%20Israel%20Is%20Carrying%20Out%20Genocide%20Is%20a%20Defining%20Moment%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F28140819%2FGEw1UHwXMAEPdVM.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3ESouth%20Africa%E2%80%99s%20case%20charging%20Israel%20with%20genocide%2C%20in%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Ficj-says-israel-must-comply-with-genocide-convention-but-stops-short-of-halting-military-operation%5C%22%3Eprovisional%20measures%20were%20announced%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20January%2026%2C%20is%20a%20marker%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%20conflict%20raging%20currently%2C%20and%20posits%20a%20moral%20prism%20to%20view%20the%20competing%20narratives.%20Raphael%20Lemkin%2C%20a%20legal%20scholar%20and%20a%20World%20War%20II%20refugee%20from%20Western%20Ukraine%20who%20lost%20considerable%20family%20in%20the%20Shoah%2C%20is%20widely%20considered%20the%20architect%20of%20the%20Genocide%20Convention%2C%20which%20was%20a%20direct%20reaction%20to%20the%20Holocaust.%20Legal%20defences%20aside%2C%20that%20the%20State%20of%20Israel%2C%20a%20state%20sanctioned%20largely%20by%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20shame%20over%20allowing%20the%20Nazi%20Holocaust%20to%20occur%2C%20today%20faces%20a%20credible%20charge%20of%20genocide%20is%20a%20tragic%20irony%20of%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELemkin%20spent%20much%20of%20the%20war%20studying%20Nazi%20documents%20and%20ordinances%20to%20analyse%20the%20motive%20underlying%20Nazi%20repression%20and%20massacres%2C%20which%20today%20we%20understand%20to%20be%20archetypically%20genocidal%2C%20including%20implementing%20%3Cem%3ELebensraum%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Ea%20colonial%20stratagem%20previously%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fsurviving-genocide-colonial-namibia%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eemployed%20by%20the%20Germans%20in%20Namibia%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20used%20to%20depopulate%20territories%20for%20settling%20Germans.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20not%20the%20seemingly%20indiscriminate%20killings%20of%20civilians%20in%20Gaza%20by%20Israeli%20bombardment%2C%20which%20may%20be%20a%20war%20crime%20in%20itself%2C%20but%20the%20motive%20behind%20it%20which%20is%20called%20into%20question%20in%20South%20Africa%E2%80%99s%20case.%20Lemkin%20in%20his%20writing%20explained%20that%20genocide%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.preventgenocide.org%2Flemkin%2Ffreeworld1945.htm%5C%22%3Erefers%20to%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20plan%20%E2%80%9Caimed%20at%20destruction%20of%20the%20essential%20foundations%20of%20the%20life%20of%20national%20groups%20so%20that%20these%20groups%20wither%20and%20die%20like%20plants%20that%20have%20suffered%20a%20blight%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FLemkinInstitute%2Fstatus%2F1714599755609718970%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELemkin%20Institute%20for%20Genocide%20Prevention%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20now%20deleted%20post%20by%20the%20%40IsraelPM%20X%20handle%20%E2%80%9Cis%20an%20expression%20of%20genodical%20intent%E2%80%9D%2C%20in%20which%20it%20was%20written%20%E2%80%9C%5Bt%5Dhis%20is%20a%20struggle%20between%20the%20children%20of%20the%20light%20and%20the%20children%20of%20darkness%2C%20between%20humanity%20and%20the%20law%20of%20the%20jungle%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20lots%20of%20other%20statements%20too%20and%20the%20question%20sought%20to%20be%20answered%20in%20the%20International%20Court%20of%20Justice%20case%20is%20whether%20the%20nature%20of%20the%20Israeli%20military%20campaign%20itself%2C%20and%2For%20the%20public%20declarations%20of%20collective%20punishment%2C%20and%2For%20the%20cutting%20off%20of%20water%2C%20food%20and%20fuel%20supplies%2C%20were%20sufficient%20for%20the%20court%20to%20prescribe%20emergency%20interim%20measures%20that%20Israel%20must%20follow.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20the%20attacks%20on%20Palestinians%20in%20the%20West%20Bank%2C%20often%20by%20or%20in%20aid%20of%20Israeli%20settlers%2C%20also%20raises%20concerns%20on%20genocidal%20intent.%20For%20its%20parts%2C%20South%20Africa%E2%80%99s%20arguments%20in%20the%20ICJ%20did%20not%20link%20the%20settlement%20policies%20in%20the%20West%20Bank%20to%20the%20situation%20in%20Gaza.%20The%20ICJ%20is%20considering%20a%20separate%20advisory%20opinion%20on%20the%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.icj-cij.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fcase-related%2F186%2F186-20231114-pre-01-00-en.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20policies%20and%20practices%20of%20Israel%20in%20the%20Occupied%20Palestinian%20Territories%2C%20including%20East%20Jerusalem%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.icj-cij.org%2Fhome%5C%22%3Epreliminary%20ruling%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20January%2026%2C%20the%20ICJ%20found%20South%20Africa%E2%80%99s%20case%20to%20be%20%E2%80%9Cplausible%E2%80%9D%2C%20or%20sufficiently%20%3Cem%3Eprima%20facie%20%3C%2Fem%3Efor%20it%20to%20direct%20provisional%20measures.%20Israel%20%E2%80%93%20which%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%20has%20said%20was%20set%20up%20to%20ensure%20that%20a%20Holocaust%20%E2%80%9Cnever%20again%E2%80%9D%20happens%20%E2%80%93%20is%20prime%20facie%20indicated%20to%20be%20in%20violation%20of%20the%20Genocide%20Convention.%20The%20ICJ%20took%20note%20of%20the%20conduct%20of%20Israeli%20forces%2C%20statements%20of%20UN%20officials%20and%20Israeli%20officials%2C%20and%20the%20situation%20in%20Gaza%20in%20itself.%20It%20also%20took%20note%20of%20the%20UN%E2%80%99s%20Committee%20on%20the%20Elimination%20of%20Racial%20Discrimination%20which%20found%20%E2%80%9Cracist%20hate%20speech%E2%80%9D%20and%20an%20expert%20group%E2%80%99s%20report%20that%20found%20%E2%80%9Cdiscernibly%20genocidal%20and%20dehumanising%20rhetoric%E2%80%9D.%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20self-declared%20steps%20to%20comply%20with%20the%20Genocide%20Convention%20were%20held%20to%20be%20insufficient%20to%20remove%20the%20risk%20of%20%E2%80%9Cirreparable%20prejudice%E2%80%9D%20to%20the%20rights%20of%20the%20Palestinian%20people%20under%20the%20Genocide%20Convention.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22By%20Invoking%20Genocide%20Convention%2C%20ICJ%20Makes%20It%20Clear%20Israel's%20Killing%20of%20Palestinians%20is%20Not%20'War'%20But%20Crime%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fby-invoking-genocide-convention-icj-makes-it-clear-israels-killing-of-palestinians-is-not-war-but-crime%5C%22%3EBy%20Invoking%20Genocide%20Convention%2C%20ICJ%20Makes%20It%20Clear%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20Killing%20of%20Palestinians%20is%20Not%20%E2%80%98War%E2%80%99%20But%20Crime%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.icj-cij.org%2Fnode%2F203452%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eseparate%20opinion%20as%20judge%20ad%20joc%20appointed%20by%20Israel%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20and%20not%2C%20as%20he%20emphatically%20notes%2C%20its%20agent%20%E2%80%93%20Aharon%20Barak%2C%20a%20former%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20the%20Israeli%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20has%20anguish%20seeping%20through%20his%20words.%20He%20evokes%20the%20memory%20of%20Lemkin.%20Barak%20was%20a%20five%20year%20old%20when%20Nazis%20put%20him%20with%20his%20family%20in%20a%20ghetto%2C%20and%20he%20is%20himself%20a%20survivor%20of%20the%20genocide%20in%20Lithuania.%20He%20writes%20that%20%E2%80%9C%5Bg%5Denocide%20is%20more%20than%20a%20word%20for%20me%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20the%20%E2%80%9Cidea%20that%20Israel%20is%20now%20accused%20of%20committing%20genocide%20is%20very%20hard%20for%20me%20personally%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%20His%20statement%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cevery%20Israeli%20soldier%20carries%20with%20him%20(or%20her)%20in%20their%20backpack%2C%20the%20rules%20of%20international%20law%E2%80%9D%20will%20jar%20those%20watching%20the%20bombardment%20live.%20However%2C%20even%20though%20Barak%20finds%20no%20plausible%20links%20to%20genocidal%20intent%2C%20he%20struggles%20with%20the%20situation%20and%20votes%20for%20humanitarian%20aid%20and%20the%20direction%20to%20stop%20incitement%20to%20genocide%20%E2%80%93%20the%20latter%20to%20%E2%80%9Cdecrease%20tensions%20and%20discourage%20damaging%20rhetoric%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20a%20make%20or%20break%20moment%20in%20international%20law.%20Although%20no%20state%20has%20formally%20joined%20the%20case%20with%20South%20Africa%2C%20the%20divide%20in%20those%20indicating%20support%20and%20those%20against%20runs%20through%20a%20global%20north-south%20divide.%20Of%20the%20BRICS%20countries%2C%20Brazil%20has%20supported%20South%20Africa%20explicitly%2C%20and%20Russia%20and%20China%20have%20been%20sympathetic.%20India%20has%20been%20silent%20on%20the%20case.%20The%20global%20north%20has%20come%20out%20against%20the%20case%20itself%2C%20and%20as%20traditional%20exponents%20of%20what%20they%20call%20the%20international%20%E2%80%98rules-based%20order%E2%80%99%2C%20countries%20such%20as%20Germany%2C%20which%20has%20referred%20to%20the%20historical%20necessity%20to%20support%20Israel%2C%20are%20faced%20with%20difficult%20choices.%20Canada%20has%20been%20another%20vocal%20supporter%20of%20Israeli%20actions%2C%20in%20contrast%20to%20its%20oft%20stated%20position%20as%20a%20stronger%20supporter%20of%20international%20law.%20However%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.eeas.europa.eu%2Feeas%2Ficj-joint-statement-high-representative-and-european-commission_en%5C%22%3EEU%20Commission%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20quick%20to%20announce%20after%20the%20order%20that%20ICJ%20judgments%20are%20binding%20and%20it%20expects%20compliance.%20This%20can%20only%20lead%20to%20a%20churn%20in%20the%20international%20system%2C%20and%20a%20shift%20towards%20more%20%3Cem%3Ereal%20politik%20%3C%2Fem%3Eor%20a%20passing%20of%20some%20of%20the%20power%20enjoyed%20by%20traditional%20exponents.%20South%20Africa%E2%80%99s%20role%20in%20bringing%20the%20case%20is%20in%20itself%20indicative%20of%20that%20shift.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20bringing%20the%20case%2C%20South%20Africa%20is%20not%20just%20exercising%20its%20legal%20right%20as%20a%20signatory%20to%20the%20Genocide%20Convention%2C%20but%20also%20discharging%20an%20obligation%20flowing%20from%20the%20moral%20authority%20of%20Nelson%20Mandela%2C%20who%20was%20an%20ardent%20supporter%20of%20the%20Palestinian%20cause%2C%20and%20considered%20himself%20in%20solidarity%20with%2C%20and%20in%20debt%20to%2C%20the%20Palestinian%20leadership%20for%20its%20support%20of%20the%20African%20National%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20struggle%20against%20apartheid.%20Consistent%20with%20this%20history%20was%20Israel%20and%20Apartheid%20South%20Africa%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3Ereal%20politik%20%3C%2Fem%3Emutual%20support.%20There%20are%20also%20suggestions%20that%20South%20Africa%E2%80%99s%20case%20is%20due%20to%20the%20need%20to%20shore%20up%20domestic%20support%20for%20President%20Cyril%20Ramaphosa%2C%20but%20it%20is%20hard%20to%20argue%20that%20South%20Africa%E2%80%99s%20motives%20are%20strictly%20cynical.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESouth%20Africa%E2%80%99s%20right%20to%20bring%20a%20case%20was%20a%20particularly%20Lemkinesque%20insertion%20into%20the%20Genocide%20Convention%2C%20which%20made%20the%20crime%20of%20genocide%20a%20crime%20against%20all%20humanity%20%E2%80%93%20%3Cem%3Ehostis%20generis%20humani%20%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%93%20thereby%20making%20it%C2%A0the%20duty%20of%20every%20country%20to%20prevent%20such%20actions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22What%20Explains%20the%20Desensitisation%20of%20the%20Western%20Leadership%20Towards%20Horrors%20in%20Gaza%3F%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fwhat-explains-the-desensitisation-of-the-western-leadership-towards-horrors-in-gaza%5C%22%3EWhat%20Explains%20the%20Desensitisation%20of%20the%20Western%20Leadership%20Towards%20Horrors%20in%20Gaza%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIsrael%20has%20been%20ordered%20to%20not%20carry%20out%20genocide%2C%20to%20disallow%20and%20prosecute%20the%20public%20and%20direct%20incitement%20to%20genocide%2C%20to%20allow%20humanitarian%20aid%2C%20and%20to%20report%20to%20the%20court%20with%20a%20copy%20to%20South%20Africa%20within%2030%20days.%20The%20court%20has%20no%20sheriff%20it%20can%20send%20to%20coerce%20compliance%2C%20but%20is%20a%20moral%20expression%20of%20international%20law%3B%20Israel%20and%20its%20supporters%20will%20find%20their%20arguments%20harder%20to%20make%20now%20that%20the%20ICJ%20has%20said%20there%20is%20a%20%3Cem%3Eprima%20facie%20%3C%2Fem%3Ecase%20of%20genocide%20they%20are%20answerable%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Israeli%20State%20now%20faces%20a%20choice%20%E2%80%93%20probably%20being%20articulated%20by%20many%20of%20its%20supporters%20%E2%80%93%20of%20hunkering%20down%20into%20an%20us-versus-the-rest-of-the-world%20mindset%2C%20and%20accusing%20the%20court%20of%20being%20a%20backer%20of%20terror%2C%20or%20of%20travelling%2C%20or%20be%20forced%20to%20travel%2C%20down%20the%20hard%20path%20to%20a%20re-think.%20The%20early%20signs%20are%20not%20encouraging.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAvi%20Singh%20is%20an%20advocate%20who%20specialises%20in%20transnational%20and%20international%20law%20and%20is%20a%20professor%20at%20the%20International%20University%20College%2C%20Turin.%20He%20has%20also%20practiced%20before%20international%20criminal%20tribunals.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706439207000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F28140819%2FGEw1UHwXMAEPdVM.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Ffor-the-icj-to-say-it-is-plausible-that-israel-is-carrying-out-genocide-is-a-defining-moment%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22That%20the%20State%20of%20Israel%2C%20a%20state%20sanctioned%20largely%20by%20the%20world's%20shame%20over%20allowing%20the%20Nazi%20Holocaust%20to%20occur%2C%20today%20faces%20a%20credible%20charge%20of%20genocide%20is%20a%20tragic%20irony%20of%20history.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Ffor-the-icj-to-say-it-is-plausible-that-israel-is-carrying-out-genocide-is-a-defining-moment%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Draft%20UGC%20Guidelines%20Suggest%20De-Reserving%20Faculty%20Positions%20in%20Universities%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F29095001%2FScreenshot-2023-11-29-at-9.49.41-AM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20University%20Grants%20Commission%20(UGC)%20has%20come%20up%20with%20draft%20rules%20to%20de-reserve%20the%20posts%20of%20faculty%20members%20in%20higher%20education%20institutions%20if%20%E2%80%98enough%20reserved%20candidates%20are%20not%20available%E2%80%99%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newindianexpress.com%2Fthesundaystandard%2F2024%2FJan%2F28%2Fdraft-ugc-guidelines-seek-to-open-de-reservation-window%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20New%20Indian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20guidelines%20were%20released%20in%20the%20last%20week%20of%20December.%20They%20are%20open%20for%20public%20opinion%20till%20today.%20The%20posts%20in%20question%20are%20meant%20for%20SC%2C%20ST%20and%20OBC%20categories.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGenerally%2C%20these%20posts%20can%E2%80%99t%20be%20de-reserved%20for%20unreserved%20category%20candidates.%20But%20for%20Group%20A%20posts%2C%20a%20university%20can%20prepare%20a%20proposal%20for%20de-reservation%20as%20they%20can%E2%80%99t%20be%20allowed%20to%20remain%20vacant%20in%20%E2%80%98public%20interest%E2%80%99%2C%20the%20newspaper%20quoted%20the%20draft%20guidelines%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTo%20do%20so%2C%20it%20would%20have%20to%20provide%20information%20like%20the%20designation%2C%20pay%20scale%2C%20name%20of%20the%20service%2C%20responsibilities%2C%20required%20qualifications%2C%20efforts%20made%20to%20fill%20the%20post%2C%20and%20why%20it%20cannot%20be%20allowed%20to%20remain%20vacant%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Group%20C%20and%20D%20posts%20can%20be%20de-reserved%20by%20the%20executive%20council%20of%20the%20university%20itself%20while%20for%20Group%20A%20posts%2C%20the%20proposal%20has%20to%20be%20submitted%20to%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Education.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20guidelines%20would%20apply%20to%20all%20the%20central%20universities%2C%20deemed-to-be-universities%2C%20and%20other%20autonomous%20bodies%2Finstitutions%20under%20the%20central%20government%20or%20those%20receiving%20grant-in-aid%20from%20the%20UGC%2C%20central%20government%2C%20or%20consolidated%20fund%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20rules%20would%20apply%20in%20promotion%20policies%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20draft%20rules%20argued%20that%20there%20has%20been%20a%20shortfall%20in%20reserved%20category%20posts%20and%20the%20institutions%20should%20fill%20the%20vacant%20posts%20by%20starting%20a%20recruitment%20drive%20for%20the%20second%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706435942000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F29095001%2FScreenshot-2023-11-29-at-9.49.41-AM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fdraft-ugc-guidelines-suggest-de-reserving-faculty-positions-in-universities%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22These%20rules%20would%20apply%20in%20promotion%20policies%2C%20too.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A13%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fdraft-ugc-guidelines-suggest-de-reserving-faculty-positions-in-universities%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%5D